name: ChemotherapyAndBiotherapyWithPotentialToCauseGrade3OrHigherFatigue
title: Chemotherapy and Biotherapy with Potential to Cause Grade 3 or Higher Fatigue
purpose:
(Clinical Focus: This value set contains RxNORM concepts for various chemotherapy and biotherapy agents, regardless of dosage or administration route.),(Data Element Scope: Various drugs used in the treatment of cancer which may cause fatigue.),(Inclusion Criteria: altretamine, bendamustine, busulfan, chlorambucil, cisplatin, cyclophosphamide, ifosfamide, mechlorethamine, melphalan, oxaliplatin, temozolomide, thiotepa, azacitidine, cladribine, clofarabine, cytarabine, decitabine, floxuridine, fludarabine, fluorouracil, mercaptopurine, nelarabine, pemetrexed, pentostatin, pralatrexate, thioguanine, dactinomycin, mitomycin, mitoxantrone, daunorubicin, daunorubicin citrate liposomal, doxorubicin, doxorubicin liposomal, epirubicin, idarubicin, abemaciclib, arsenic trioxide, hydroxyurea, ixabepilone, midostaurin, procarbazine, ribociclib, romidepsin, omacetaxine, carmustine, lomustine, etoposide, teniposide, docetaxel, paclitaxel protein-bound particles, vinblastine, vincristine, vinorelbine, topotecan, interferon alfa-2b, interferon gamma-1b, erlotinib, nilotinib),(Exclusion Criteria: Brand name drugs and drug packs. 
Checkpoint inhibitors which may cause fatigue.)
